com.camerontec.catalys.core.session.persistence

Class MemoryPersister

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.util.configuration.registry.Registerable
      • com.camerontec.catalys.core.session.persistence.MemoryPersister
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IFIXSessionStatePersister, IConfigurable, IRegisterable

    public class MemoryPersister
extends Registerable
    Memory based implementation of the IFIXSessionStatePersister interface.

    This is also a useful base class for other IFIXSessionStatePersister implementations. It can provide memory caching of persistent data.

      • getOutMessages

        public List<IFIXMessage> getOutMessages(int beginSeq,
                                        int endSeq)
                                 throws IOException
        Recover all messages that have been sent with sequence numbers between the given limits (inclusive).

        The sequence numbers use the FIX 4.2 convention of 0 for SEQ_NUMBER_INFINITY.

        Parameters:
        beginSeq - Sequence number to start from
        endSeq - Sequence number to end with
        Returns:
        List of all messages between two sequence numbers, or empty list, if none found.
        Throws:
        IOException - if an I/O error occurs when accessing persisted data.
        See Also:
        FIXSequenceNumberConstants.SEQ_NUMBER_INFINITY

      • clearOutMessages

        public void clearOutMessages()
                      throws IOException
        Clear all messages that have been sent that are not needed any more - for example, when sequence numbers are reset.

        Note that because the last output message number is deduced from the list of output messages, this has the effect of making OutMsgSeqNum -1. In other words, immediately after this method has been called IFIXSessionStatePersister.getPersistedOutMsgSeqNum() should return -1.

        Throws:
        IOException - if an I/O error occurs when accessing persisted data.

      • configure

        public final void configure(IConfiguration configuration)
                     throws ConfigurationException
        Apply the IConfiguration to this IConfigurable.

        This method is called by the configuration module in the server:

        • when loading the configuration at server startup (e.g. when reading the XML configuration file) and
        • every time we reload the configuration object corresponding to the configurable run-time object.
        The Catalys Server passes a reference to a configuration clone. The original reference is unavailable to the configurable object. The configurable object may decide to store the reference as the last valid configuration object which can be used to optimize the re-configuration.
        Specified by:
        configure in interface IConfigurable
        Parameters:
        configuration - the immutable configuration object
        Throws:
        ConfigurationException - This exception is thrown when the new configuration object cannot be applied to the configurable object.

        protected final void persistSelectedOutMessage(IFIXMessage message)
                                        throws IOException
        Checks that the sequence number of the message to be persisted is greater than the last persisted sequence number. If so delegate to doPersistSelectedOutMessage(com.camerontec.catalys.core.message.IFIXMessage). Otherwise print an error message and ignore the message.
